WEBVTT

00:01:29.637 --> 00:01:32.946
Modern-day eyeglasses
feature a pair of rims

00:01:32.970 --> 00:01:34.905
that hold corrective lenses,

00:01:34.929 --> 00:01:37.363
a bridge that connects the rims,

00:01:37.387 --> 00:01:39.988
sides that slide behind the ears,

00:01:40.012 --> 00:01:42.988
hinges that connect
the sides to the frames,

00:01:43.012 --> 00:01:46.238
and on some glasses, a pair of temple tips

00:01:46.262 --> 00:01:48.196
for behind the ear comfort.

00:01:48.220 --> 00:01:49.530
In American culture,

00:01:49.554 --> 00:01:52.863
20th century cinema
helped popularize eyeglasses.

00:01:52.887 --> 00:01:56.613
Audiences would see
glamorous actresses and actors

00:01:56.637 --> 00:01:59.613
donning glasses
to take on a different persona.

00:01:59.637 --> 00:02:02.113
Sometimes a pair of glasses
became popularized